This article is misleading and has omitted information and exaggerated info too. Christians aren't banned from celebrating Christmas in Brunei. In fact, Christmas is officially a public holiday in Brunei and has been so for decades. Something the media 'conveniently' omits in the articles ---- anti-Brunei articles, may I add. In Brunei, Christians are allowed to practice their religions in their homes, churches and communities. What is banned, however, is extravagant public Xmas celebrations (and decorations). Otherwise, it is permissible for Christians to celebrate it. SUMMARY: Brunei doesn't ban other faiths from celebrating their customs and traditions. 25th Dec - still a public holiday. Media is bias.
